{"TopicId":181044,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How to calculate launch to make sat on polar orbit around the Mun","CreatedByName":"Pawelk198604","CreatedById":35539,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-01T22:34:03Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Pawelk198604","CreatedById":35539,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-01T22:34:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI need it to put it along Mun Polar orbit like here at the end of video,\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/Bkj3GbZSS2s?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-01T23:29:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe simplest, but probably not the most efficient solution: Go for the Mun as always, don\u0027t even bother with making it equatorial, make it as eccentric ad possible at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ascending Node\u0022\u003EAN\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Descending Node\u0022\u003EDN\u003C/abbr\u003E, change inclination to polar at the highest \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ascending Node\u0022\u003EAN\u003C/abbr\u003E (make sure you do it in correct direction, otherwise you\u0027d be going retrograde to desired orbit) and fine-tune it to demanded specs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pawelk198604","CreatedById":35539,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-02T01:38:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223514652\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221546385392\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Aziz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, The Aziz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe simplest, but probably not the most efficient solution: Go for the Mun as always, don\u0027t even bother with making it equatorial, make it as eccentric ad possible at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ascending Node\u0022\u003EAN\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Descending Node\u0022\u003EDN\u003C/abbr\u003E, change inclination to polar at the highest \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ascending Node\u0022\u003EAN\u003C/abbr\u003E (make sure you do it in correct direction, otherwise you\u0027d be going retrograde to desired orbit) and fine-tune it to demanded specs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI made it but thanks \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/oyv4c3rezZE?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003Efrom 50 minute\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-02T01:55:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know how to \u0022Calculate\u0022 it but you can do it quite easily with maneuver nodes. Eject to Mun as normal, and then plop a maneuver node halfway there. Send it north or south a bit so you pass above or below Mun, and radial/prograde to pass directly under or over a pole. Bam. Done.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAdvanced mode: You can acutally do this with the ejection burn.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-02T11:38:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223514700\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221546394102\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know how to \u0022Calculate\u0022 it but you can do it quite easily with maneuver nodes. Eject to Mun as normal, and then plop a maneuver node halfway there. Send it north or south a bit so you pass above or below Mun, and radial/prograde to pass directly under or over a pole. Bam. Done.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAdvanced mode: You can acutally do this with the ejection burn.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyes, it can be smart to test out first that is cheapest, note that you have to aim for center of mun and not behind it as you usually do for orbits.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pecan","CreatedById":96332,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-02T12:36:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is nothing to calculate.\u00A0 Go to Mun any time and make the intercept a polar one.\u00A0 Circularise into polar orbit; job done.\u00A0 If you want a polar Mun orbit normal to Kerbin you\u0027re out of luck because it will change over the course of a Mun month.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-02T18:25:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMoving to Gameplay Questions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Draalo","CreatedById":158993,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-02T19:25:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWait in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Low Kerbin Orbit\u0022\u003ELKO\u003C/abbr\u003E until Mun has moved ~45\u00B0 forward.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlan your transferburn, aim for Muns center.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs soon as you entered Muns \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E burn (anti)normal till your PE is at the designated orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCircularise and do an inklination correction till the contract orbit is matched.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDone \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223514854\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221546432582\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002296332\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pecan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Pecan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCircularise\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E into\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E polar\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E orbit\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E; job \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Edone\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E.\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope, he has to match an orbit from a contract \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Goody1981","CreatedById":153740,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-02T20:43:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor a slightly more accurate method (so that you actually arrive at the Mun at close to the correct inclination) you have to eject from\u00A0Kerbin when your target orbit at the Mun is lined up along the Mun\u2019s orbit path (can focus view on the Mun the check).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it is, eject, and when you arrive at the Mun (1/4 of the Mun\u2019s orbit later), the target orbit will now be lined up with your incoming path (perpendicular to the Mun\u2019s orbit path).\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFinetune your arrival (well before you get there) so that you either pass above the North Pole, or below the South Pole, depending on the\u00A0direction of the required orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-02T23:57:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223515047\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221546457126\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022158993\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Draalo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Draalo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope, he has to match an orbit from a contract \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh. He never said that. \u0022How do I do a polar orbit\u0022 and \u0022how do I complete a satellite contract\u0022 are two different questions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pawelk198604","CreatedById":35539,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-03T03:51:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/tVwpQ18EK1Q?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Draalo","CreatedById":158993,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-03T13:35:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223515181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221546473473\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh. He never\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E said that\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHe did, was a bit hidden in the last 20s of his first video.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway, my advice related to another orbit which could be seen, so my advice was also wrong.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFortunately he managed it anyway \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}